==English==

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/'wɒtʃ/}}
*{{audio|en-us-watch.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɒtʃ|-ɒtʃ]]

===Etymology===
Old English ''[[wæċċe]]''.

====Noun====
{{en-noun|es}}

# {{time}} A [[portable]] or [[wearable]] [[timepiece]].
# {{time}} A particular time period where guarding is kept.
# A person or group of people who guard.
# {{nautical}} A group of sailors and officers aboard a ship or shore station with a common period of duty: ''starboard watch'', ''port watch''.
# {{nautical}} A [[period]] of [[time]] on [[duty]], usually four hours in length; the officers and crew who [[tend]] the [[working]] of a [[vessel]] during the same watch. (FM 55&ndash;501).

